        <fields>
            <name>S01_Instructions</name>
            <fieldText>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Instructions:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tightness Test:ï»¿&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;1) Raise the pressure top 7/10 millibar (mb) for 1 minute to test the let by of the ECV.1. If the let by is susceptive, then disconnect the regulator and apply the leak detection fluid (LDF) inside the ECV.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2) If let by is present, then contact the gas transporter.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;3) Raise the pressure to 20 millibar for 1 minute for the stabilisation period.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;4) For a further 2 minutes, test the installation at 20mb.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leak Test:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;1) Apply LDF to unions and test points after the testing procedure.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2) Ensure that test point is correctly inserted and tightened as appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;3) LDF will bubble if there is an escape present.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;4) Leave sufficient time for LDF to react , around 2 minutes. Ensure consideration is given to all the new and existing connections for signs of leakage.&lt;/p&gt;</fieldText>
            <fieldType>DisplayText</fieldType>
        </fields>
